cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel consensus notion for distributed Gaussian mixture probability hypothesis density fusion based on a decentralized sensor network. This involves communication and fusion computation, which suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Control Systems (cs.SY). The paper also involves the merging of Gaussian components, which suggests that it could belong to the category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves the use of covariance and averaging, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
